I have a deep respect for my culture and its customs. I learned a great deal of wisdom from my parents and have a strong sense of honor and responsibility that I strive to fulfill.

My clothing is traditional, often a long-sleeved tunic, with loose pants tucked into my leather sandals. Most days I wear a white turban to match my clothing.

In my spare time I enjoy working in my family garden, going to the bazaar and fishing in the harbor.

I am a very kind-hearted person, deeply loyal to my family and friends. I believe in justice, hospitality and compassion and always strive to be a man of integrity.
